      "valid_scope": "section_pair",
      "why_conflicting": "Two sections in the same document specify different inactivity timeout durations for sessions: 48 hours (Authentication) versus 24 hours (Session Termination). An implementation must choose one value, and end-users or auditors reading either section alone will receive incorrect information.",
      "why_llm_cannot_decide": "Neither the Purpose (smoke-check fixture for spec-anchor CLI) nor the Core Concept (minimal sample to verify LLM generation paths) specifies an authoritative timeout value. Both sections are in the same source document with no precedence rule stated. Choosing the correct value requires the human specification owner to decide which number is intentional."
    }
  ],
